Over a nineteen months period, nasopharyngeal washes and oropharyngeal swabs specimens were obtained from all patients with acute lower respiratory tract infection episodes admitted to the Paediatric Emergency Department of La Paz Hospital, a tertiary care hospital in Madrid, Spain. The results of the IC Adeno Respiratory Card Letitest were compared with those obtained by multiplex RT-PCR and viral culture. The applicability of the assay for routine adenovirus testing is discussed. 


